Lupin Gets Tentative Approval from FDA for Irbesartan Tablets

-- B y   A d i   N a r a y a n
-- 
2011-10-10T06:26:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-10/lupin-gets-tentative-approval-from-fda-for-irbesartan-tablets.html
Lupin Ltd. (LPC) , the world’s largest
maker of anti-tuberculosis medicines, received tentative
approval from the U.S. Food and Drug Administration for its
irbesartan drug to treat hypertension, according to a statement
on the regulator’s website.  The tablet is a generic version of Avago, which is jointly
marketed by Sanofi and Bristol-Myers Squibb Co.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Adi Narayan in  Mumbai  at 
 anarayan8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
